Devdiscourse News Desk | Amaravati | India
Residents across Andhra Pradesh brace for intense heatwave conditions, as the state disaster management authority issues warnings for 64 mandals.
Temperatures soared past 41°C in several districts, with Piduguralla recording a sweltering 45.9°C. Relief may come this weekend as clouds and possible rain are anticipated.
Citizens are urged to take stringent precautions, and authorities caution outdoor workers and residents against heat-related risks and thunderstorms.
(With inputs from agencies.)
